ast night and took a chance.<br>
<br>
Was fighting a warrior in Freeport and he had me down to one bubble while he kept getting healed--rotten bugger had friends--so I figured it was time to head for zone.  I cornered the City Hall, with him on my heels, and hit sneak/hide...which he noticed.  Then I got jumpy with my mouse and clicked on the main door--it opened, as usual... and he ran through it, thinking he's chasing a hidden rogue.<br>
<br>
*blink, blink*<br>
<br>
Broke hide and ran like hell for the zone.<br>
<br>
Confusion...just another way to survive and fight another day.<br>
<br>
-Sterk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/teenyknot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/01 1:45:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/Fricka_on_vallon_zek/FrickaNEW.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Obvious Trick Against Melee's</span><hr size=1> Works wonders too near zone lines.  Hide right before the zone and they think you've gone through. <p><table border=0 align=left width=100%>
